Three men; Olubunmi Oladeji, Raphael Kajopinola and Akande Lawal on Tuesday appeared before an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court in Lagos, for allegedly breaking into a car and stealing N305,000. <img class="size-full wp-image-1265514 aligncenter" src="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=640%2C360&#038;ssl=1" alt="INEC, Court adjourns Ex-UNILAG lecturer rape trial" width="640" height="360" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=1024%2C576&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=200%2C113&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=560%2C315&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The defendants, ages 50, 57 and 57 respectively, are standing trial for alleged conspiracy, breaking in and stealing. The trio committed the offences on April 12, at a filling station in Ijora Badia, Lagos, the Prosecutor, ASP Ezekiel Ayorinde told the court. He said that the defendants conspired to break into a Nissan Pathfinder SUV belonging to Mr Abass Lawal and stole his money. “The complainant came to buy fuel and after filling his tank, he told the defendants who were fuel attendant and security guards, to watch after his car that he wanted to buy something across the road. “But when he returned, he discovered that his car had been burgled and the N305, 000 he kept in a polythene bag had been stolen. “The complainant reported the case and the defendants were arrested,’’ the prosecutor said. The alleged offences contravened sections 287, 307, and 411of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that section 287 prescribes three years jail term for stealing while section 307 attracts seven-year for breaking in. Following their pleas of not guilty, Magistrate Mrs B.O Osunsanmi released the defendants on bail in the sum of N30, 000 each with two sureties each in like sum. Osunsanmi said that all the sureties should be gainfully employed and show evidence of two years tax payment to the Lagos State Government (LASG). Further hearing has been fixed for Dec. 11. Vanguard An Ikeja Magistrates’ Court in Lagos on Tuesday admitted a hair stylist, Valentine Ogiugo to bail in the sum of N10,000 bail, for allegedly stealing a N5,000 phone. February 19, 2019 In "News" THREE men, who allegedly assaulted the executives of Aso Rock Community Development Association, CDA, and their security guard by stabbing them with broken bottles and inflicting injuries on their bodies, have been arraigned before an Ejigbo Chief Magistrate’s Court in Lagos. February 14, 2018 In "Crime Guard" Lagos — Two security guards of Igbosere Magistrate’s Court and a Tricycle rider, were yesterday arraigned before the court for allegedly stealing 103 copies of Law reports valued N1.5million, the property of Lagos State Judiciary. The defendants are Lateef Bello, 53, Oyedokun Afeez, 27 and Tajudeen Igbekoya, 34.  They were charged… December 1, 2017 In "News"